# Virtual Card Service ‚Äî Feature Rules

> Generic FinTech guardrails (money/Decimal, sensitive-data logging, audit trails, idempotency, auth, SQL safety, testing) live in the repo-root **`.cursor/rules/fintech-safe-defaults.mdc`** and always apply. This file adds only what is specific to the virtual-card feature.

Read `homework-3/specification.md` before making any changes. Every rule below is derived from that spec.

## Card State Machine

- All card status transitions must go through `apply_status_transition`. No ad-hoc `if status == X: status = Y` assignments.
- Allowed transitions: `ACTIVE ‚Üí FROZEN`, `FROZEN ‚Üí ACTIVE`, `ACTIVE ‚Üí CLOSED`, `FROZEN ‚Üí CLOSED`.
- `CLOSED` is terminal. Never permit any transition out of `CLOSED`.
- Invalid transitions raise `CardStateTransitionError`, surfaced as HTTP 409.

## Card Data Handling ‚Äî PAN and CVV2

- Never store a raw PAN in the application database. Persist only the non-reversible card token and the masked PAN (`masked_pan`, `****-****-****-XXXX`, exposing at most the last four digits).
- Never add a database column named `pan`, `card_number`, `raw_pan`, `cvv`, or `cvv2` (any variant). Reject such migrations.
- CVV2 lives only in the encrypted DB column and the one-time `POST /cards` 201 response. Never return CVV2 from any GET endpoint ‚Äî assert `GET /cards/{id}` has no `cvv2` field.
- `masked_pan` is the only PAN representation allowed in responses and logs.

## Endpoints and Role Routing

- Role ‚Üí path map: `USER` ‚Üí `/cards/*` only; `SUPPORT` ‚Üí `/support/*` only; `OPS_COMPLIANCE` ‚Üí `/ops/*`, `/support/*`, and card lookups. A `USER` request to `/ops/*` or `/support/*` returns HTTP 403 immediately.
- The support card view is a dedicated `/support/*` endpoint (spec Task 18); do not grant `SUPPORT` access to `/cards/*`.
- Every state-mutating endpoint (`POST /cards`, `PUT /cards/{id}/status`, `PUT /cards/{id}/limits`) must handle the `Idempotency-Key` header (mechanics in the global rule).
- Audit `actor_type` for this feature is one of `USER | OPS | SUPPORT | SYSTEM`.

## External Services

- Calls to `user-service`, `token-vault`, and `encryption-service` use a 2-second timeout; on timeout return HTTP 503 and commit no partial state (per the global secrets/external-calls rule).

## Migrations (SQLAlchemy 2.x + Alembic)

- `audit_events` table must have indexes on `(card_id, timestamp)` and `(user_id, timestamp)`.
- Foreign key `transactions.card_id ‚Üí cards.id` with `ON DELETE RESTRICT` (never cascade-delete transactions).
- No foreign-key cascade from `cards` to `audit_events` (audit records survive card closure).

## What Never to Do (feature-specific)

- Never bypass `apply_status_transition` for a status change.
- Never add a route that returns CVV2 after initial card creation.
- Never add a `pan`/`cvv2`/`card_number` column to any card table.
